      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>US dollar gains against Japanese yen as lack of confidence in Japan's economy leads to sell-off in its stock market, discouraging demand for its currency; dollar closes at 109.71 yen, up from 109.17; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>THE YEN FALLS. The dollar gained against the yen as a lack of confidence in Japan's economy led to a sell-off in its stock market, discouraging demand for its currency. The dollar closed at 109.71 yen, up from 109.17 Thursday.</p>
      </block>
